<TITLE> 1500 investigations pending with ACC </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 16 (bdnews24.com) The Anticorruption Commission (ACC) currently has over 1,500 pending investigations relating to charges of misappropriation of money, bribery and extortion, and illegal acquisition of wealth. Some 836 cases and 808 allegations are under investigation in total, ACC director general Col Hanif Iqbal said in a regular briefing on Monday The ACC has filed 1,216 cases over the last two years, since Hasan Mashhud Chowdhury took over as chairman on Feb 25 2007 up to Jan 31 this year, said Iqbal. "Of the total cases, 341 were filed by the Commission and 495 by police or other agencies." Some 156 cases have seen convictions, 521 cases are under trial charge sheets of about 151 cases are under process, the rest are still under investigation, said Iqbal. Of the cases under trial, five special courts in Dhaka are trying 81, said the ACC official. The higher courts have stayed 645 cases, of which 301 were later withdrawn while 344 stays remain, he added. "The Commission has also served wealth statement notices on a total of 436 persons during the period," he said. "Of them, 335 submitted their accounts and 90 more are expected. Eleven failed to furnish their accounts, 6 of them were convicted for it." "A proposal for amendment to ACC laws has been returned by the cabinet for further explanation. The proposal will be sent back to the cabinet with explanation in a few days," said Iqbal. bdnew
